---
layout: layouts/component-demo.njk
title: Five-Face Rating Picker
description: a picker for selecting a 1-5 satisfaction rating using face labels
---

{% from "components/five-face-rating-picker/macro.njk" import fiveFaceRatingPicker %}
{% from "components/five-face-rating-picker-button/macro.njk" import fiveFaceRatingPickerButton %}

<h2>How satisfied were you?</h2>
{% call fiveFaceRatingPicker({ label: "How satisfied were you with your visit?" }) %}
  {{ fiveFaceRatingPickerButton({ value: 1 }) }}
  {{ fiveFaceRatingPickerButton({ value: 2 }) }}
  {{ fiveFaceRatingPickerButton({ value: 3 }) }}
  {{ fiveFaceRatingPickerButton({ value: 4, checked: true }) }}
  {{ fiveFaceRatingPickerButton({ value: 5 }) }}
{% endcall %}

<h2>Rate your experience</h2>
{% call fiveFaceRatingPicker({ label: "Rate your experience" }) %}
  {{ fiveFaceRatingPickerButton({ value: 1 }) }}
  {{ fiveFaceRatingPickerButton({ value: 2 }) }}
  {{ fiveFaceRatingPickerButton({ value: 3 }) }}
  {{ fiveFaceRatingPickerButton({ value: 4 }) }}
  {{ fiveFaceRatingPickerButton({ value: 5 }) }}
{% endcall %}

<h2>Accessibility</h2>
<p>The picker is a <code>&lt;div role="radiogroup"&gt;</code> with
  an <code>aria-label</code>. Each button inside is a
  <code>&lt;button role="radio"&gt;</code> that sets
  <code>aria-checked</code> when selected; unselected buttons
  render desaturated in the example CSS.</p>
